CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1953, pg, 26, reads: "Proud Champions - Here are the four Negro youths who captured the Golden Gloves titles at the Gardens Tuesday night. Left to right are Reybon Stubbs, who defended his 147 pound title... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Golden Gloves boxing champion Reybon Stubbs wearing shorts with NY logo and tying shoe, in Duquesne Gardens with broadsides advertising hockey
